theorem Topology.closure_interior_closure_eq_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} (hP3 : Topology.P3 (X := X) A) :
    closure (interior (closure A)) = closure A := by
  apply subset_antisymm
  · -- `closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A`
    exact closure_mono (interior_subset : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A)
  · -- From `P3`, we have `A ⊆ interior (closure A)`
    have h_sub : A ⊆ interior (closure A) := hP3
    -- Taking closures preserves inclusions.
    exact closure_mono h_sub

theorem Topology.closure_interior_union_subset_union_closure_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (interior (A ∪ B)) ⊆
      closure (interior A) ∪ closure (interior B) := by
  -- We apply `closure_minimal`, showing that the right-hand side
  -- is a closed set containing `interior (A ∪ B)`.
  apply closure_minimal
  · -- First, prove the inclusion
    --   `interior (A ∪ B) ⊆ closure (interior A) ∪ closure (interior B)`.
    intro x hx
    -- Rewrite the membership using `interior_union`.
    have hx' : x ∈ interior A ∪ interior B := by
      simpa [interior_union] using hx
    -- Each interior is contained in the corresponding closure.
    cases hx' with
    | inl hxA =>
        exact Or.inl (subset_closure hxA)
    | inr hxB =>
        exact Or.inr (subset_closure hxB)
  · -- Finally, check that the target set is closed.
    have h₁ : IsClosed (closure (interior A)) := isClosed_closure
    have h₂ : IsClosed (closure (interior B)) := isClosed_closure
    exact h₁.union h₂

theorem Topology.interior_closure_interior_subset_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure (interior A)) ⊆ closure A := by
  intro x hx
  -- First, `x` lies in `closure (interior A)`.
  have hx₁ : x ∈ closure (interior A) :=
    interior_subset hx
  -- Monotonicity of `closure` turns `interior A ⊆ A` into
  -- `closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A`, so `x ∈ closure A`.
  have hx₂ : x ∈ closure A :=
    (closure_mono (interior_subset : interior A ⊆ A)) hx₁
  exact hx₂
